Information Gathering and Enumeration Lab
Objective

To perform reconnaissance, enumeration, and vulnerability assessment on a target system in a controlled laboratory environment.

Tools Used

* Nmap
* SMBClient
* Enum4linux
* theHarvester
* Nessus
* Kali Linux

Activities Performed

Host Discovery
Performed host discovery to determine whether the target system was active and reachable.

Service Detection
Conducted service and version detection to identify exposed network services.

SMB Enumeration
Attempted enumeration of SMB services, shares, users, and system information.

Open-Source Intelligence (OSINT)
Used theHarvester to collect publicly available information related to the target domain.

Vulnerability Assessment
Configured and executed a Nessus vulnerability scan to identify security weaknesses.

Results

* Confirmed target availability.
* Gathered service information.
* Identified publicly accessible resources.
* Performed vulnerability assessment using Nessus.
* Documented findings and observations.

Skills Demonstrated

* Information Gathering
* OSINT
* Network Enumeration
* Service Enumeration
* SMB Enumeration
* Vulnerability Assessment
* Security Analysis

Screenshots

* Host Discovery Results
* Service Detection Results
* SMB Enumeration Results
* theHarvester Results
* Nessus Scan Results

Disclaimer

This project was conducted in a controlled laboratory environment for educational and ethical cybersecurity training purposes only.
